    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix NULL pointer dereference in UL SCH PDU packing functions\n\n### Summary\nThe UL SCH PDU packing functions in the NFAPi implementation were missing NULL pointer checks, causing segmentation faults when called with invalid parameters. This issue was observed during stress testing of the 5G NR stack when processing malformed UL configuration requests.\n\nThe bug caused the gNB to crash intermittently under high load conditions when the P7 packing functions received NULL pointers due to memory allocation failures in the FAPI interface layer.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p7.c`: Added NULL pointer validation to `pack_ul_config_request_ulsch_rel8_value`, `pack_ul_config_request_ulsch_rel10_value`, `pack_ul_config_request_ulsch_rel11_value`, and `pack_ul_config_request_ulsch_rel13_value` functions.\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Configure gNB with aggressive UL scheduling parameters\n2. Run continuous traffic load test for >30 minutes\n3. Observe intermittent segmentation fault in `nfapi_p7_message_pack` function\n4. Core dump analysis shows crash in `pack_ul_config_request_ulsch_rel8_value` when accessing NULL pointer\n\nThe issue occurs more frequently when the system is under memory pressure and the FAPI interface layer fails to allocate PDU structures properly.\n"
}